Description: nostalgic Mystify display hack for XScreenSaver
 A lightweight Xlib recreation of the Windows 95/98 Mystify Your Mind
 screensaver. Two colorful deforming wire polygons bounce around the screen,
 retaining and incrementally erasing old outlines.
 .
 It uses integer motion and plain X11 drawing without OpenGL, XRender, GTK,
 alpha blending, or full-frame animation copies, making it suitable for older
 Unix workstations and low-end computers.

